data.title: Famous Logician: Georg Henrik von Wright
data.meta_description: Georg Henrik von Wright was a Finnish philosopher, who succeeded Ludwig Wittgenstein as professor at the University of Cambridge. Georg Henrik von Wright was a Finnish philosopher, who succeeded Ludwig Wittgenstein as professor at the University of Cambridge.

Name: Georg Henrik von Wright

Born: 14 June 1916

Deathplace: Helsinki, Finland

School: Analytic philosophy

Main interests: Modal logic, philosophy of action, philosophy of language, philosophy of mind, philosophy of science

Institutions: University of Helsinki
